The device concept is illustrated in Fig. 1a. Two dual antiphase patch antennas (Fig. 1b), described in the text below, are placed on both flat sides of the wrist close to the position of the ulnar head under an applied controlled pressure of 1 kg force. The radiofrequency signal in the 0–2 GHz band travels from the transmit antenna through bone, cartilage, and soft tissue to the received antenna while being attenuated and scattered. The total amount of attenuation and scattering is measured via the microwave transmission coefficient \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
