				\begin{document}$${S}_{21}(f)$$\end{document}S21(f) and is correlated to osteopenic and osteoporotic conditions. The antenna width across the wrist is 2 cm; the antenna length along the wrist is 5 cm; facilitating good contact between the two surfaces.Figure 1
(a) Idealized diagram illustrating antenna placement on both sides of a human wrist. (b) Transmit and receive dual antiphase patch antennas with individual lumped-component matching networks (green isolation) designed for the present study. Antenna length (along the wrist) is 5 cm; antenna width (across the wrist) is 1.8 cm.

